From: Thor Thayer <tthayer@opensource.altera.com>
Date: Tue, 10 Mar 2015 12:06:08 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 118/172] FogBugz #270904-16: A10SYCON: Enable GPIO & HWMON by
 default

This patch enables the GPIO (and by extension the LEDs and
pushbuttons reads) as well as the HW Monitor module by default
on our board because the GHRD will need this functionality.

Signed-off-by: Thor Thayer <tthayer@opensource.altera.com>
[czou:Original patch taken from
https://github.com/altera-opensource/linux-socfpga.git socfpga-4.1]
Signed-off-by: czou <cao.zou@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm/configs/socfpga_defconfig | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm/configs/socfpga_defconfig b/arch/arm/configs/socfpga_defconfig
index 3f6ea1e..df5ed76 100644
--- a/arch/arm/configs/socfpga_defconfig
+++ b/arch/arm/configs/socfpga_defconfig
@@ -143,3 +143,5 @@ CONFIG_DETECT_HUNG_TASK=y
 CONFIG_FUNCTION_TRACER=y
 CONFIG_DEBUG_USER=y
 CONFIG_XZ_DEC=y
+CONFIG_GPIO_A10SYCON=y
+CONFIG_SENSORS_A10SYCON=y
